I wasn’t going to share our miscarriage story because our page is always about laughter and joy and I didn’t want to make anyone sad. But I knew when God told me it was the right time that I would help someone with what we went through.

I honestly thought I would never go through something like this so don’t ever think you are too big or healthy to deal with something like this.

Our miscarriage is called blighted ovum. This means that the sperm fertilize the egg then the fertilized egg moved into my uterus, but as it was forming into an embryo something went wrong, and it never formed into an embryo but the sack in my uterus continued to grow, that’s why in the ultrasound you see a big sack but no baby grew in it.

We are so much better now! I am back to myself again and this a reminder be kind to people because you never know what they are going through🤍👼🏽💕🙏🏽

Love you my people my people!!!!
